Definition.WordDefinition: Psychologic \Psy`cho*log"ic\, Psychological \Psy`cho*log"ic*al\, a. [Cf. F. psychologique.] Of or pertaining to psychology. See Note under {Psychic}. -- {Psy`cho*log"ic*al*ly}, adv. [1913 Webster]

psychologically adv 1: with regard to psychology; "war that caught them in its toils either psychologically or physically"; "the event was very damaging to the child psychologically1" 2: in terms of psychology; "classify poetry psychologically"
